import sys
from awsglue.transforms import *
from awsglue.utils import getResolvedOptions
from pyspark.context import SparkContext
from awsglue.context import GlueContext
from awsglue.job import Job
  
sc = SparkContext.getOrCreate()
glueContext = GlueContext(sc)
spark = glueContext.spark_session
job = Job(glueContext)
dyf = glueContext.create_dynamic_frame.from_catalog(database='transformed flat philly', table_name='item_location')
dyf.printSchema()
df = dyf.toDF()
df.show()
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from collections import Counter
from matplotlib import rcParams
rcParams.update({'figure.autolayout': True})
location_counter = Counter()
most_common_locations = {}

pandasDF = df.toPandas()

for index, row in pandasDF.iterrows():
    item = row["item_location_lvl1"]
    try:
        location_counter[item] += 1
    except KeyError:
        print("")
# print(location_counter)
for place in location_counter:
    if location_counter[place] > 20:
        most_common_locations[place] = location_counter[place]
locations = pd.Series(most_common_locations)
# locations = pd.Series(location_counter)
locations.sort_values(ascending=True).plot(kind="barh")


job.commit()
